HighChartsSeriesOptions should have the access to the same properties as the Series Chart object. 

Based on http://api.highcharts.com/highcharts#series 

"The actual series to append to the chart. In addition to the members listed below, any member of the plotOptions for that specific type of plot can be added to a series individually. For example, even though a general lineWidth is specified in plotOptions.series, an individual lineWidth can be specified for each series."

This means the SeriesOptions should have access to properties such as color, animation etc which exist in the series chart object.

title: Refactor react.d.ts, merging with react-addons.d.ts
body:
This PR is broadly inspired by the official React DOM Terminology (http://facebook.github.io/react/docs/glossary.html). The main interfaces are: - `ReactElement

`created using `React.DOM` factories and `React.createElement` in `render()`. Contains `type`, `props`, `key`, and `ref`. - `ComponentClass

`created using `React.createClass` from `ComponentSpec`. - `Factory

`created using `createFactory

` from `ComponentClass

`. Produces `ReactElement

` when called with props `P`. - `Component

`only available from `React.render` at the top-level. Contains Component API methods such as `getDOMNode()` and `setProps()`. The `React` module is now separated into sections roughly corresponding to the sections in the React Reference (`Top-Level API`, `Component API`, `Component Specs and Lifecycle`, `Event System`, etc.). - added: `interface XEventHandler` as shorthand for `(event: React.XEvent) => void` - fixed: `refs` has type `{ [key: string]: Component }`, not `Component

` - added: types for `HTMLAttributes` and `SVGAttributes` (annotated with `//` where union types are desired) - added: `batchedUpdates` to `react/addons` - updated: typing for `addons.update` - added: more tests to `react-tests.ts` cc @pspeter3

body:
